OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FAfter a bitingly cold few days, with
OL,7,Ftemperatures struggling into the low
OL,8,Fsingle figures by day and dipping
OL,9,Fbelow freezing overnight, the UK's
OL,10,Fweather is about to shift dramatically
OL,11,Fwith daytime highs soaring by more
OL,12,Fthan ten degrees in some areas.
OL,14,FCoupled with warm, spring sunshine and
OL,15,Fa light breeze, this is the good news
OL,16,Fthat we all really need at the moment!
OL,18,FWhy is the weather turning warmer and
OL,19,Fsunnier?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FThe main reason is high pressure
OL,7,Fbuilding across the UK.
OL,9,FOver the last few days, Atlantic
OL,10,Ffrontal systems have swept in across
OL,11,Fthe UK from the west, bringing spells
OL,12,Fof rain and heavy, blustery showers,
OL,13,Fwhile a cold westerly wind has dragged
OL,14,Fin a bitter airmass which has dragged
OL,15,Fdaytime temperatures down and given
OL,16,Fnorthern areas a return of the wintry
OL,17,Fconditions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FA dominant area of high pressure
OL,7,Fbuilds in across the UK from the east
OL,8,Fthroughout Tuesday, holding back the
OL,9,Fadvance of those rain-bearing frontal
OL,10,Fsystems while a shift in wind
OL,11,Fdirection to the east/south-east drags
OL,12,Fin much milder air from the near
OL,13,Fcontinent. There should be plenty of
OL,14,Fsunshine, too.
OL,16,FWhy does high pressure bring more
OL,17,Fsettled weather?JUnder high-pressure
OL,18,Fair slowly sinks rather than rises.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FThat sinking air suppresses cloud
OL,7,Fformation, allowing more sunshine to
OL,8,Fdevelop. (Having said that, there are
OL,9,Foccasions where cloud gets 'trapped'
OL,10,Funder high pressure, which gives a
OL,11,Fsettled but rather cloudy and stagnant
OL,12,Fperiod of weather - but we're not
OL,13,Fexpecting this week to be one of those
OL,14,Foccasions).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FSo with more sunshine and a warmer
OL,7,Fairmass, forecasters expect a dramatic
OL,8,Frise in temperatures. It's the
OL,9,Fopposite of low pressure, where rising
OL,10,Fair encourages clouds, showers, and
OL,11,Fstronger winds. It's the opposite of
OL,12,Flow pressure, where rising air
OL,13,Fencourages clouds, showers, and
OL,14,Fstronger winds.
OL,16,FHow warm could it actually get?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FTemperatures are expected to climb
OL,7,Fsteadily through the week. The Met
OL,8,FOffice suggests many places could
OL,9,Freach the mid to high teens, and if
OL,10,Fsunshine is prolonged, some areas
OL,11,Fcould even approach around 18`20C,
OL,12,Fwhich would give many areas their
OL,13,Fwarmest day of the year so far. Values
OL,14,Flike this are well above the UK
OL,15,Faverage for early spring, and in
OL,16,Fsunny, sheltered spots, it could feel
OL,17,Feven warmer.
OL,19,FWhere will we see the best sunshine?
OL,26,@sD@aOX
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773667695
OL,3,CSpring surge: UK temperatures set to
OL,4,Csoar ` but how warm could it get?
OL,6,FThe bulk of the UK should see some
OL,7,Flovely weather from the middle of next
OL,8,Fweek, with the best sunshine expected
OL,9,Fto be across southern and eastern
OL,10,Fparts of the UK, where skies are most
OL,11,Flikely to stay clear.
OL,13,FWestern areas could still see a little
OL,14,Fmore cloud at times, particularly if
OL,15,FAtlantic weather systems brush the
OL,16,Fedge of the high-pressure system, but
OL,17,Feven with a little more cloud here,
OL,18,Fsome very pleasant days lie ahead.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
